Air quality is dened as a measure of the condition of air relative to the requirements of one or more bioticspecies or to any human need or purpose. To compute AQI requires an air pollutant concentration form a monitor or model.

Air quality is considered satisfactory, and air pollution poses little or no risk
Air quality is acceptable; however, for unusually sensitive people should consider limiting prolonged outdoor exertion.

Members of sensitive groups may experience health effects. People with heart or lung disease, older adults, and children should avoid heavy exertion outdoor. The general public should limit prolonged outdoor activities

Members of sensitive groups may experience serious health effects. People with heart or lung disease, older adults, and children should avoid outdoor activities. The general public may begin to experience health effects and should avoid heavy exertion outdoor.

Health warnings of emergency conditions for the entire population. People with heart or lung disease, older adults, and children should remain indoor. The general public should avoid prolonged or heavy exertion outdoor.
Low pollution without any bad effect on health. No restriction for outdoor activities to the public. Maintain healthy lifestyle.
Moderate pollution that does not pose any bad effect on health. No restriction for outdoor activities to the public. Maintain healthy lifestyle.

Worsen the health condition of high risk people who is the people with heart and lung complications. Limited outdoor activities for the high risk people. Public need to reduce the extreme outdoor activities.

Worsen the health condition and low tolerance of physical exercises to people with heart and lung complications. Affect public health. Old and high risk people are advised to stay indoor and reduce physical activities. People with health complications are advised to see doctor.
Hazardous to high risk people and public health. Old and high risk people are prohibited for outdoor activities. Public are advised to prevent from outdoor activities.
Hazardous to high risk people and public health. Public are advised to follow orders from National Security Council and always follow the announcement in mass media.

Particles with diameters less than 10 micro meters can get deep into the lungs when in haled. They can aggravate lung and heart diseases, and lead to symptoms such as chest discomfort, wheezing, shortness of breath, car diac arrhythmias and heart attacks. Long-term exposures have been linked to the develop ment of lung and heart diseases.

Particles with diameter less than 2.5 micrometers can get deep into the respiratory tract, reaching the lungs. Exposure to fine particles can cause short-term health effects such as eye, nose, throat and lung irritation, coughing, sneezing, runny nose and shortness of breath. Exposure to fine particles can also affect lung function and worsen medical conditions such as asthma and heart disease.
